        <mxCell id="igFG3KY3LtFasvbX7WE--9" value="Higher player count increases the acquisition of primary, secondary, and tertiary resources:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Economic resources, Strategic resources (items, experience, neutral structures, map control)&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This factor is also affected by races, heroes, map design (creep routes, item availability)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Can heavily snowball games into the 2nd forces&#39; favor, as they will collective spend less &lt;u&gt;time&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;to acquire &lt;u&gt;more&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;resources&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Increased number of players allows for diversification of investments towards specific resources&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some players can compete for creeps, items, map control, while others focus on economic resources&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Cooperative attacks minimize risk on resource losses to increase the cost of enemy&#39;s actions (creeping, tech timers, etc.)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;darkOpacity=0.05;fontSize=20;" vertex="1" parent="1">
